[
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000005_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000005_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Whether the Soul Knows Bodies Through the Intellect?",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000006_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000006_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Objection one: It would seem that the soul does not know bodies through the intellect.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000006_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000006_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But such are not bodies.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000006_000005",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000006_000005.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the soul cannot know bodies through the intellect.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000007_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000007_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But the soul can by no means, through the senses, understand spiritual things, which are intelligible.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000007_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000007_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore by no means can it, through the intellect, know bodies, which are sensible.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000008_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000008_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But all bodies are mobile and changeable. Therefore the soul cannot know bodies through the intellect.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000009_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000009_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "If, therefore, the intellect does not know bodies, it follows that there is no science of bodies; and thus perishes natural science, which treats of mobile bodies.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000010_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000010_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "And because they observed that all bodies are mobile, and considered them to be ever in a state of flux, they were of opinion that we can have no certain knowledge of the true nature of things.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000012_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000012_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Now this may be shown to be false for two reasons.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000012_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000012_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "First, because, since those species are immaterial and immovable, knowledge of movement and matter would be excluded from science (which knowledge is proper to natural science), and likewise all demonstration through moving and material causes.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000014_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000014_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But there is no necessity for this.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000014_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000014_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "For even in sensible things it is to be observed that the form is otherwise in one sensible than in another: for instance, whiteness may be of great intensity in one, and of a less intensity in another: in one we find whiteness with sweetness, in another without sweetness.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000014_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000014_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "So also the intellect, according to its own mode, receives under conditions of immateriality and immobility, the species of material and mobile bodies: for the received is in the receiver according to the mode of the receiver.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000014_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000014_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "We must conclude, therefore, that through the intellect the soul knows bodies by a knowledge which is immaterial, universal, and necessary.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000015_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000015_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "For the intellect knows bodies by understanding them, not indeed through bodies, nor through material and corporeal species; but through immaterial and intelligible species, which can be in the soul by their own essence.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000019_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000019_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Whether the Soul Understands Corporeal Things Through Its Essence?",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000020_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000020_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Objection one: It would seem that the soul understands corporeal things through its essence.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000020_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000020_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the soul knows bodies through its essence, which it employs for the formation of such images, and from which it forms them.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000022_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000022_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore all corporeal creatures exist in a more excellent way in the soul than in themselves.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000022_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000022_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the soul can know corporeal creatures through its essence.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000023_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000023_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore it does not know corporeal things through itself.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000024_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000024_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "For it was universally admitted that \"like is known by like.\" But they thought that the form of the thing known is in the knower in the same mode as in the thing known.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000024_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000024_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "The Platonists however were of a contrary opinion.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000024_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000024_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "For Plato, having observed that the intellectual soul has an immaterial nature, and an immaterial mode of knowledge, held that the forms of things known subsist immaterially.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000024_000006",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000024_000006.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Lastly, Empedocles, who held the existence of our four material elements and two principles of movement, said that the soul was composed of these. Consequently, since they held that things exist in the soul materially, they maintained that all the soul's knowledge is material, thus failing to discern intellect from sense.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000025_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000025_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But this opinion will not hold.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000025_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000025_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "First, because in the material principle of which they spoke, the various results do not exist save in potentiality.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000025_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000025_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Secondly, because if it were necessary for the thing known to exist materially in the knower, there would be no reason why things which have a material existence outside the soul should be devoid of knowledge; why, for instance, if by fire the soul knows fire, that fire also which is outside the soul should not have knowledge of fire.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000026_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000026_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "We must conclude, therefore, that material things known must needs exist in the knower, not materially, but immaterially.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000026_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000026_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "The reason of this is, because the act of knowledge extends to things outside the knower: for we know things even that are external to us.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000026_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000026_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Now by matter the form of a thing is determined to some one thing.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000026_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000026_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Wherefore it is clear that knowledge is in inverse ratio of materiality.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000026_000006",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000026_000006.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the intellect which abstracts the species not only from matter, but also from the individuating conditions of matter, has more perfect knowledge than the senses, which receive the form of the thing known, without matter indeed, but subject to material conditions.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000027_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000027_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "It is therefore clear from the foregoing, that if there be an intellect which knows all things by its essence, then its essence must needs have all things in itself immaterially; thus the early philosophers held that the essence of the soul, that it may know all things, must be actually composed of the principles of all material things.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000027_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000027_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Now this is proper to God, that His Essence comprise all things immaterially as effects pre exist virtually in their cause. God alone, therefore, understands all things through His Essence: but neither the human soul nor the angels can do so.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000028_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000028_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "To the formation of such images the soul gives part of its substance, just as a subject is given in order to be informed by some form.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000028_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000028_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "In this way the soul makes such images from itself; not that the soul or some part of the soul be turned into this or that image; but just as we say that a body is made into something colored because of its being informed with color.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000028_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000028_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "That this is the sense, is clear from what follows.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-high_s-slow_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "high",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000028_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000028_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "For he says that the soul \"keeps something\"--namely, not informed with such image-\"which is able freely to judge of the species of these images\": and that this is the \"mind\" or \"intellect.\" And he says that the part which is informed with these images-namely, the imagination-is \"common to us and beasts.\"",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000032_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000032_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Whether the Soul Understands All Things Through Innate Species?",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000033_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000033_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Objection one: It would seem that the soul understands all things through innate species.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000034_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000034_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But primary matter was created by God under the forms to which it has potentiality.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000034_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000034_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore much more is the intellectual soul created by God under intelligible species.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000034_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000034_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "And so the soul understands corporeal things through innate species.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000035_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000035_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore we have some knowledge of things even before we acquire knowledge; which would not be the case unless we had innate species.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000035_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000035_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the soul understands corporeal things through innate species.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000037_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000037_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Now we observe that man sometimes is only a potential knower, both as to sense and as to intellect.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000037_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000037_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "And he is reduced from such potentiality to act-through the action of sensible objects on his senses, to the act of sensation-by instruction or discovery, to the act of understanding.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000037_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000037_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Wherefore we must say that the cognitive soul is in potentiality both to the images which are the principles of sensing, and to those which are the principles of understanding.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000038_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000038_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But since that which has a form actually, is sometimes unable to act according to that form on account of some hindrance, as a light thing may be hindered from moving upwards; for this reason did Plato hold that naturally man's intellect is filled with all intelligible species, but that, by being united to the body, it is hindered from the realization of its act.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000038_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000038_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But this seems to be unreasonable.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000038_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000038_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "First, because, if the soul has a natural knowledge of all things, it seems impossible for the soul so far to forget the existence of such knowledge as not to know itself to be possessed thereof: for no man forgets what he knows naturally; that, for instance, the whole is larger than the part, and such like.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000038_000007",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000038_000007.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "We must therefore conclude that the soul does not know corporeal things through innate species.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000039_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000039_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "In the same way the angelic intellect is perfected by intelligible species, in accordance with its nature; whereas the human intellect is in potentiality to such species.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000040_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000040_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "On the other hand, the intellect does not receive substantial being through the intelligible species; and therefore there is no comparison.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000043_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000043_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Whether the Intelligible Species Are Derived by the Soul from Certain Separate Forms?",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000044_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000044_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Objection one: It would seem that the intelligible species are derived by the soul from some separate forms.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000044_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000044_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "For whatever is such by participation is caused by what is such essentially; for instance, that which is on fire is reduced to fire as the cause thereof.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000044_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000044_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore what in itself and in its essence is understood in act, is the cause that the intellectual soul actually understands.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000044_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000044_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Now that which in its essence is actually understood is a form existing without matter.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000044_000005",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000044_000005.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the intelligible species, by which the soul understands, are caused by some separate forms.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "very high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000045_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000045_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But the sensible species which are in the senses, and by which we sense, are caused by the sensible object which exists actually outside the soul.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000045_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000045_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the intelligible species, by which our intellect understands, are caused by some things actually intelligible, existing outside the soul.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000045_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000045_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But these can be nothing else than forms separate from matter.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000045_000004",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000045_000004.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the intelligible forms of our intellect are derived from some separate substances.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "very fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000046_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000046_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "If, therefore, our intellect, previously in potentiality, afterwards actually understands, this must needs be caused by some intellect which is always in act.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-low",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "low"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000046_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000046_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But this is a separate intellect.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "very fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000046_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000046_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Therefore the intelligible species, by which we actually understand, are caused by some separate substances.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000047_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000047_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "And this is proved to be false especially from the fact that if a man be wanting in a sense, he cannot have any knowledge of the sensibles corresponding to that sense.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000048_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000048_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "And this in two ways.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-slow_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "slow",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000048_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000048_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Now participation of an idea takes place by some image of the idea in the participator, just as a model is participated by a copy.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000049_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000049_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Consequently he does not hold that the soul has innate knowledge, as Plato, who held that the participated ideas remain immovably in the soul.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000050_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000050_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But in this opinion no sufficient reason can be assigned for the soul being united to the body.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000050_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000050_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "For it cannot be said that the intellectual soul is united to the body for the sake of the body: for neither is form for the sake of matter, nor is the mover for the sake of the moved, but rather the reverse.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000050_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000050_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Especially does the body seem necessary to the intellectual soul, for the latter's proper operation which is to understand: since as to its being the soul does not depend on the body.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000050_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000050_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But if the soul by its very nature had an inborn aptitude for receiving intelligible species through the influence of only certain separate principles, and were not to receive them from the senses, it would not need the body in order to understand: wherefore to no purpose would it be united to the body.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000051_000000",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000051_000000.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "But if it be said that our soul needs the senses in order to understand, through being in some way awakened by them to the consideration of those things, the intelligible species of which it receives from the separate principles: even this seems an insufficient explanation.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000051_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000051_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Consequently the reason of the union of the soul with the body still remains to be sought.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "normal"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000052_000002",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000052_000002.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "And thus a man born blind could have knowledge of colors; which is clearly untrue.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-normal_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "normal",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000052_000003",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000052_000003.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "We must therefore conclude that the intelligible species, by which our soul understands, are not derived from separate forms.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-high",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "high"
    },
    {
        "item_name": "LibriTTS_R-8632_245697_000054_000001",
        "wav_path": "/apdcephfs_qy3/share_1474453/shuoyizhou/data_preprocess/LibriTTS-R/LibriTTS_R/8632/245697/8632_245697_000054_000001.wav",
        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-8632",
        "content": "Wherefore there is no comparison between sense and intellect.",
        "style_prompt": "M_p-normal_s-fast_e-normal",
        "gender": "M",
        "pitch": "normal",
        "speed": "fast",
        "energy": "normal"
    }
]